<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="420" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,757,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
1. Body dark fuscous, vertex bicolored (tannish caudally, fuscous distally), wings patterned, lacking 
<emphasis box="[1179,1195,758,779]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">ir</emphasis>
crossvein (
<emphasis box="[1308,1332,758,779]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">im</emphasis>
also missing); flagellum large bearing four long sclerotized processes.................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett, 2021" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2021" box="[1047,1436,787,809]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baynardi">
<emphasis box="[1047,1199,787,808]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">Myxia baynardi</emphasis>
Bahder &amp; Bartlett, 2021
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,757,1073]" box="[151,1436,816,838]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,816,838]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
1’. Body whitish or yellow, vertex pale, not bicolored; wings clear, 
<emphasis box="[841,857,817,838]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">ir</emphasis>
crossvein present................................ 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,757,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
2. Body uniformly yellow, face without markings, periandrium with large retrorse spine and two subapical anterior angled spines............................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Bahder &amp; Bartlett, 2019" authorityName="Bahder &amp; Bartlett" authorityYear="2019" box="[1060,1436,875,897]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belinda">
<emphasis box="[1060,1198,875,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">Myxia belinda</emphasis>
Bahder &amp; Bartlett, 2019
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,757,1073]" box="[151,1436,904,926]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,904,926]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">2’. Body whitish, face with white markings and orange patch traversing median carina................................ 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,757,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
3. Aedeagal shaft in ventral view with one fin-shaped process on right lateral side (
<bibRefCitation author="Bahder, B. W. &amp; Bartlett, C. R. &amp; Barrantes, E. A. B. &amp; Zumbado, M. A. Z. &amp; Humphries, A. R. &amp; Helmick, E. E. &amp; Goss, E. M. &amp; Ascunce, M. S." box="[998,1189,933,955]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420" pagination="65 - 81" refId="ref6204" refString="Bahder, B. W., Bartlett, C. R., Barrantes, E. A. B., Zumbado, M. A. Z., Humphries, A. R., Helmick, E. E. Goss, E. M. &amp; Ascunce, M. S. (2019 a) A new genus and species of cixiid planthopper (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Fulgoroidea) from the Reserva Privada el Silencio de Los Angeles Cloud Forest in Costa Rica. Zootaxa, 4701 (1), 65 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4701.1.5" type="journal article" year="2019">Bahder et al. 2019a</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 8C), a single process at endosomal apex, medioventral process of pygofer more rounded (
<bibRefCitation author="Bahder, B. W. &amp; Bartlett, C. R. &amp; Barrantes, E. A. B. &amp; Zumbado, M. A. Z. &amp; Humphries, A. R. &amp; Helmick, E. E. &amp; Goss, E. M. &amp; Ascunce, M. S." box="[880,1071,963,985]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420" pagination="65 - 81" refId="ref6204" refString="Bahder, B. W., Bartlett, C. R., Barrantes, E. A. B., Zumbado, M. A. Z., Humphries, A. R., Helmick, E. E. Goss, E. M. &amp; Ascunce, M. S. (2019 a) A new genus and species of cixiid planthopper (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Fulgoroidea) from the Reserva Privada el Silencio de Los Angeles Cloud Forest in Costa Rica. Zootaxa, 4701 (1), 65 - 81. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4701.1.5" type="journal article" year="2019">Bahder et al. 2019a</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 7B).................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kramer, 1979)" baseAuthorityName="Kramer" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[1168,1436,992,1014]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta">
<emphasis box="[1168,1282,992,1014]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">Myxia delta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer, J. P." box="[1294,1429,992,1014]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420" pagination="301 - 389" refId="ref7420" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1979) Taxonomic study of the planthopper genus Myndus in the Americas (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea: Cixiidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 105 (3), 301 - 389." type="journal article" year="1979">Kramer, 1979</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,757,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="420">
3’. Aedeagal shaft with two fin-shaped processes, one on each side (
<figureCitation box="[862,947,1021,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1250,1274]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,181,1226]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[232,1355,181,1226]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Aedeagus and phallobase of Myxia hernandezi sp. n.: (A) left lateral view, (B), right lateral view, (C) dorsal view, and (D) ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449785" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449785/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">Figs. 5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[959,990,1021,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[228,1351,1341,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-47@7.[226,1361,1334,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Line art of aedeagus and phallobase of Myxia hernandezi sp. n.: (A) left lateral view, (B), right lateral view, (C) dorsal view, and (D) ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449789/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">6C</figureCitation>
), two processes at endosomal apex (
<figureCitation box="[1347,1424,1021,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[228,1351,1341,1954]" captionTargetId="figure-47@7.[226,1361,1334,1958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. Line art of aedeagus and phallobase of Myxia hernandezi sp. n.: (A) left lateral view, (B), right lateral view, (C) dorsal view, and (D) ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449789" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449789/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
), medioventral process of pygofer triangular (
<figureCitation box="[650,723,1051,1073]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[171,1436,1036,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-41@6.[148,1439,1035,1900]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Figure 4. Male terminalia of Myxia hernandezi sp. n.; (A) lateral view, (B), ventral view, and (C) dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5449783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5449783/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="420">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
)...................................... 
